WHAT IS A SERVER?
-A server is a computer or system that provides functionality to other devices or program known as client throught a network, it serves request, processes data and facilitates communication between clients and servers.

-WHAT ARE THE ROLE OF DOMAIN NAME?
-Domain name such as (www.footbar.com) helps in identifying/acess websites throught their numerical IP Addresses.

WHAT TYPE OF DNS RECORD  www is in www.footbar.com
-A Record

What is the role of the web server
-The web server is to store, process and deliver web pages and other web content to users.

What is the role of the application server
-Application servers receive incoming requests from clients and process.

What is the role of the database
-Data base is use for data storage, Manipulaton and data retrival.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
-It uses the IP Address

ISSUES WITH THE INFRASTRUCTURE
-Since the infrastructure has only one server, when the server goes down, the website becomes inaccessable, and any hardware failure will lead to down timefor the website.
To resolve this problem, we can use multiple server.

